cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with generative models of images and disentangling appearance and perspective in images. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a Variationally Inferred Transformational Autoencoder (VITAE) that incorporates a spatial transformer into a variational autoencoder. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with learning compact and easy-to-interpret factors of the data. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper deals with spatial transformations of images. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network-based model for disentangled representation learning.
